          About

          Description

          The Russo-Ukrainian War is an ongoing war between Russia and Ukraine. It began in February 2014 following the Ukrainian Revolution of Dignity, and initially focused on the status of Crimea and parts of the Donbas, internationally recognised as part of Ukraine. Wikipedia
          Start date: February 20, 2014 Trending
          Location: Ukraine, Crimean Peninsula, Eastern Ukraine, MORE
